	<section id="presentation_audio" expanded="true">
		<audio id="narration01">
			<file play="true" duration="171" bytes="58583" startpos="1">a_04_02_02_040_01.swf</file>
			<transcript translate="true">Parents can use emotional moments as opportunities to connect with their child. Many parents can share a child's happiness when they have learned a new skill. However, it can be hard not to feel frustrated with a child who throws a tantrum in the grocery store.</transcript>
			<notes id="mentor-character">Narrator:</notes>
		</audio>
		<audio id="narration02">
			<file play="false" duration="135" bytes="45983" startpos="1">a_04_02_02_040_02.swf</file>
			<transcript translate="true">These emotional moments are when children need to turn to adults and caregivers for guidance. The response they receive from a trusted caregiver can have a dramatic effect on the way they behave.</transcript>
			<notes id="mentor-character">Narrator:</notes>
		</audio>
		<audio id="narration03">
			<file play="false" duration="88" bytes="29819" startpos="1">a_04_02_02_040_03.swf</file>
			<transcript translate="true">One great way to connect is to talk to your child at eye level. Get down on your knees and speak to them while looking at them.</transcript>
			<notes id="mentor-character">Narrator:</notes>
		</audio>
		<audio id="narration04">
			<file play="false" duration="131" bytes="44687" startpos="1">a_04_02_02_040_04.swf</file>
			<transcript translate="true">Parents aren't perfect so it is common for parents to make mistakes in their interactions with children. Explain your mistakes, repair the interaction, and reconnect with the child.</transcript>
			<notes id="mentor-character">Narrator:</notes>
		</audio>
		<audio id="narration05">
			<file play="false" duration="158" bytes="54059" startpos="1">a_04_02_02_040_05.swf</file>
			<transcript translate="true">Whether happy or sad, children's emotions offer parents three very important opportunities: To understand the child. To build a deeper and more trusting relationship. And to teach children about feelings.</transcript>
			<notes id="mentor-character">Narrator:</notes>
